  "prompt": "Can non-profit organizations pay a salary?",
  "response": "Yes, non-profit organizations can pay salaries to their employees. In fact, many non-profit organizations have paid staff to manage operations, provide services, and fulfill their mission. Paying salaries allows non-profits to attract and retain qualified personnel to effectively run the organization and achieve their goals.\n\nThe key requirement is that the salaries must be reasonable and in line with what is necessary for the organization to compete in the job market, and they must be justified in the context of the organization's financial resources and commitment to its mission. Non-profits must comply with IRS regulations and avoid excessive compensation, as this could jeopardize their tax-exempt status.",
